  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Ruby on Mac]]></title>
    <link href="http://clonehulk.github.io/blog/2013/06/06/Ruby-on-Mac/"/>
    <updated>2013-06-06T19:07:00+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://clonehulk.github.io/blog/2013/06/06/Ruby-on-Mac</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>The default version of Ruby on Mac OXS is 1.8.7. But the Ruby Rails needs Ruby 1.9.3 or further. So we need update it.</p>

<p>Here is the notes about updating Ruby on Mac.</p>

<!-- more -->


<ol>
<li>Installing <a href="https://rvm.io/">RVM(Ruby Version Manager)</a> for upgrading Ruby on OXS:</li>
</ol>


<figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'>curl -L get.rvm.io | bash -s stable
</span><span class='line'>  
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<ol>
<li>Using this command to show all the available versions of Ruby.</li>
</ol>


<figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="n">rvm</span> <span class="n">list</span> <span class="n">known</span>
</span><span class='line'>  
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<ol>
<li>Installing one particular version, for example:</li>
</ol>


<figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="n">rvm</span> <span class="n">install</span> <span class="n">ruby</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">9</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">3</span>
</span><span class='line'>  
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<ol>
<li>Or if you just want the latest (current) version:</li>
</ol>


<figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="n">rvm</span> <span class="n">install</span> <span class="n">current</span> <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class="n">rvm</span> <span class="n">use</span> <span class="n">current</span>
</span><span class='line'>  
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Please note that don&rsquo;t uninstall the default version of Ruby on Mac.</p>
]]></content>
